g.text: - Actions (Create, Read, Update, Delete, Approve, ... etc)
Policy-neutral access-control mechanism defined around roles and privileges
- Creates a natural flow in the business for providing access to ‘groups’ of users with similar roles
- Allow users to gain access to multiple systems simultaneously based on predefined roles
Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC) provides access to users based on who they are rather than what they do
- Role can have access to multiple unique Resources
- Resource can have multiple unique actions applied
- Action can restrict access to resource based on conditions
- Action can restrict access to resource attributes
- Child will merge its resources with parent resources
- Child actions will override parent actions (Including fields and conditions)
- Child will inherit parent priority if it has not priority
- Child priority will override parent priority
- Inhirtance relationship is allowed upto 8 depth levels
- Actions within roles which has a high priority will override
